external_knowledge:
- "films" refers to movies;
- "filmmakers" refers to directors;
- "places where these films were made" refers to the countries where the movies were produced.

0 as an identifier in star_id, director_id, or writer_id represents the absence or anonymity of the respective movie personnel;
The highest praise refers to the highest score given by users in the rating system;
Movies in this context are part of a vast universe where some elements remain mysterious or undisclosed.

- 'Light the path to the treasure trove' is a metaphor for finding valuable information. ;
- 'Cinematic masterpieces' refers to high-quality movies. ;
- 'Action-packed sagas' are movies that are part of the action genre. ;
- 'Ranked by the brilliance of their ratings' means the movies are ordered based on their user rating scores from highest to lowest.

- 'top-rated filmmaker' means the director with the highest calculated average score of their movies; 
- 'higher than the overall movie average' refers to movies with a score above the average score of all movies in the database;
- 'particularly focusing on the achievements of the distinguished director 'James Cameron'' limits the initial selection to movies where 'James Cameron' and potentially other directors with similar achievements are considered.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM movies
WHERE released_year > 2010;
